article.description: Kalisha Keane scored 23 points, leading Michigan State (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to a 74-62 victory over Dayton on Monday night.
article.headline: Kalisha Keane scores 23 points as Spartans improve to 2-0
article.linkText: Keane helps MSU avenge 2009 loss to Dayton
article.story:
EAST LANSING, Mich. -- Kalisha Keane scored 23 points, leading Michigan State (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to a 74-62 victory over Dayton on Monday night.

Keane was 7 for 12 from the field, 3 for 5 from 3-point range and 6 for 7 from the line for the Spartans (2-0), who avenged a season-opening loss to the Flyers last season.

Cetera Washington had 13 points, while freshman Annalise Pickrel had nine points and blocked two shots when the game was close in the second half.

Michigan State shot 47.4 percent from long range and had a 27-9 advantage in points beyond the arc.

Brittany Wilson had 16 points and Justine Raterman 13 for Dayton (0-2). The Flyers lost their opener to Penn State 112-107 in double-overtime.
